Therefore, the interaction between RCC19R and Au3+ was in three stages, similar to the synthesis of glutathione protected gold nanoclusters (Fig. 3
                        ) [39]. Firstly, the RCC19R was oxidized to dimer by Au3+, while Au3+ was reduced to Au+ by phenolic hydroxyl group in the RCC19R. Immediately, OXRCC19R–Au+ and a small amount of X–Au+ (X represents anions in solution which possess weaker coordination ability to Au+ than that of OXRCC19R, such as Cl− and H2PO4
                        −) complexes formed [39]. Secondly, further redox reaction arose between X–Au+ species and a bit of secondary amine groups in the dimer. The X–Au+ transformed to Au0, and the secondary amine was oxidized to imine group. Thirdly, the AuNPs were generated after the sequestration of Au0 by OXRCC19R–Au+ complexes, owing to the strong affinity between Au+ and Au0.
